Retainer's 200k. This could take a while.

114
00:06:34.311 --> 00:06:36.522
What's a while? Three
months? Six months?

115
00:06:37.231 --> 00:06:38.875
Two. three years.

116
00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:40.919
- Jesus.
- Yeah. Southern district.

117
00:06:40.943 --> 00:06:42.486
It is what it is.

118
00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:45.465
Sure you got the money for this fight?

119
00:06:45.489 --> 00:06:46.615
He does.

120
00:06:49.868 --> 00:06:52.388
All right. Look. I gotta get back to court.

121
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:53.848
Enjoy your coffee. On me?

122
00:06:53.872 --> 00:06:55.541
So you're taking the case?

123
00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:57.644
Well. I'm gonna mull it over.

124
00:06:57.668 --> 00:06:58.937
Check the schedule.

125
00:06:58.961 --> 00:07:00.295
I'll be in touch. okay?

126
00:07:01.839 --> 00:07:04.067
- Two to three years?
- He's managing expectations.

127
00:07:04.091 --> 00:07:05.193
I can't afford him.

128
00:07:05.217 --> 00:07:08.804
Look. pay the retainer and just
watch the dominoes start to fall.

129
00:07:09.346 --> 00:07:11.616
You are being
uncharacteristically optimistic.

130
00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:13.517
You've seen what's
happening at my house.

131
00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:15.644
Optimism is the only option.

132
00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:18.145
Come on.

133
00:07:18.689 --> 00:07:20.625
Let's go get some real coffee.

134
00:07:20.649 --> 00:07:21.692
You're buying.

135
00:07:23.402 --> 00:07:24.796
You got carpet moths.

136
00:07:24.820 --> 00:07:26.214
- Carpet moths?
- Yeah.

137
00:07:26.238 --> 00:07:27.590
They lay their eggs in your rugs.

138
00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:29.509
I found larvae in pretty
much every room here.

139
00:07:29.533 --> 00:07:30.677
Jesus.

140
00:07:30.701 --> 00:07:32.345
It's a good thing you
called me when you did

141
00:07:32.369 --> 00:07:34.347
otherwise you'd have colonies here.

142
00:07:34.371 --> 00:07:36.432
- Can you get rid of them?
- Yeah.

143
00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:38.810
It'll take a few treatments.
maybe three over the next month.

144
00:07:38.834 --> 00:07:40.502
It'll cost you $9.000.

145
00:07:41.044 --> 00:07:42.689
- $9000?
- Yeah.

146
00:07:42.713 --> 00:07:45.817
Ten-five if you wanna go
with the nontoxic chemicals.

147
00:07:45.841 --> 00:07:48.278
And I'll have to take that wall
in the back of your closet down.

148
00:07:48.302 --> 00:07:50.113
And that one. at a minimum.

149
00:07:50.137 --> 00:07:51.531
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

150
00:07:51.555 --> 00:07:53.283
Look. they're in there
and they're spreading.

151
00:07:53.307 --> 00:07:56.452
First generation. best I can tell.
but if you don't get rid of them now.

152
00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:58.705
you're gonna have colonies
behind every wall in here.

153
00:07:58.729 --> 00:08:00.331
And you'll never get rid of them.

154
00:08:00.355 --> 00:08:01.875
When can you start?

155
00:08:01.899 --> 00:08:04.318
I can have a crew
here in a couple of days.

156
00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:22.252
- Thanks for the ride. Barney.
- My pleasure.

157
00:08:26.924 --> 00:08:27.925
Hey!

158
00:08:28.467 --> 00:08:29.593
Coop.

159
00:08:31.053 --> 00:08:32.739
Come to Nick's tonight.

160
00:08:32.763 --> 00:08:34.806
Come on. You could
stand to have a little fun.

161
00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:38.410
It's been over a year. Maybe
it's time to let this one go.

162
00:08:38.434 --> 00:08:40.187
He slept with my wife.

163
00:08:41.313 --> 00:08:43.565
That's true. but it's a
little reductive. isn't it?

164
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.127
Look. I'm not saying Nick didn't fuck up.

165
00:08:46.151 --> 00:08:48.630
He fucked up. She fucked up.

166
00:08:48.654 --> 00:08:51.382
But maybe you fucked up too. right?

167
00:08:51.406 --> 00:08:52.800
A little bit?

168
00:08:52.824 --> 00:08:54.260
Marriages are complicated.

169
00:08:54.284 --> 00:08:55.637
So you're saying it's my fault?

170
00:08:55.661 --> 00:08:58.473
I'm saying it doesn't
matter whose fault it is.

171
00:08:58.497 --> 00:09:00.808
We're all gonna be here
for the foreseeable future.

172
00:09:00.832 --> 00:09:02.751
Do yourself a favor and get over it.

173
00:09:03.544 --> 00:09:04.545
Would you?

174
00:09:06.088 --> 00:09:07.089
I would pretend to.

175
00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:09.466
Well. I got my kids tonight. so...

176
00:09:10.092 --> 00:09:11.444
Okay. Fair enough.

177
00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:13.154
I'll see you later. Barney.

178
00:09:13.178 --> 00:09:14.513
See you. Coop.

179
00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:25.583
My god. She's so sweet.

180
00:09:25.607 --> 00:09:28.002
Esti? She's a little demon.

181
00:09:28.026 --> 00:09:29.712
She looks like an angel.

182
00:09:29.736 --> 00:09:31.464
That's how she gets you.

183
00:09:31.488 --> 00:09:33.574
She's an evil genius.

184
00:09:34.533 --> 00:09:36.177
Hey. Andy. Your friend is here.

185
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:37.661
Hello. Coop.

186
00:09:39.538 --> 00:09:40.598
What are you doing here?

187
00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:42.249
I was in the neighborhood.

188
00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.335
- In this neighborhood?
- Figured I'd stop by.

189
00:09:45.961 --> 00:09:47.838
See if you still wanted to do business.

190
00:09:52.551 --> 00:09:57.031
Well. I am going to hit the shower
and leave you to your business.

191
00:09:57.055 --> 00:09:58.741
It was so nice to meet you. lu.

192
00:09:58.765 --> 00:09:59.892
You too. Ali.

193
00:10:00.559 --> 00:10:02.162
Break a leg tonight.

194
00:10:02.186 --> 00:10:03.896
Thank you.

195
00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:08.251
Nice girl. your sister.

196
00:10:08.275 --> 00:10:09.460
What are you doing in my house?

197
00:10:09.484 --> 00:10:10.628
I came for the watch.

198
00:10:10.652 --> 00:10:12.589
Thought you said you couldn't move it.

199
00:10:12.613 --> 00:10:14.966
I had to be sure you weren't a cop.

200
00:10:14.990 --> 00:10:16.176
So I looked into you.

201
00:10:16.200 --> 00:10:17.677
You looked into me?

202
00:10:17.701 --> 00:10:21.055
Rich guy loses his big
job with his big hedge fund.

203
00:10:21.079 --> 00:10:24.058
Suddenly has big liquidity problems.

204
00:10:24.082 --> 00:10:27.353
You could have sold your Maserati.
but what would the neighbors think

205
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:30.940
if Andrew Cooper was
suddenly driving a c-class?

206
00:10:30.964 --> 00:10:35.069
So. the Princeton finance
superstar turns to petty crime.

207
00:10:35.093 --> 00:10:37.197
You have no idea what
you're talking about.

208
00:10:37.221 --> 00:10:39.449
The Richard Mille watch.

209
00:10:39.473 --> 00:10:42.368
It isn't yours. but it came
from this neighborhood.

210
00:10:42.392 --> 00:10:44.496
Bradley sperling.

211
00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:46.688
Couple of streets over from here.

212
00:10:47.648 --> 00:10:51.503
It took me one phone call to trace
the serial number on the watch.

213
00:10:51.527 --> 00:10:54.339
find out who bought
it and where they live.

214
00:10:54.363 --> 00:10:57.926
Nothing so dangerous as someone
who doesn't know what they don't know.

215
00:10:57.950 --> 00:10:59.159
Am I right?

216
00:10:59.743 --> 00:11:02.913
But what you do know
is I know where you live.

217
00:11:03.872 --> 00:11:05.707
I know where your family lives.

218
00:11:08.210 --> 00:11:09.354
Are you threatening me?

219
00:11:09.378 --> 00:11:11.189
Don't think of it as a threat.

220
00:11:11.213 --> 00:11:14.692
It's more of a contract really.

221
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:19.239
that says if you get caught you
won't talk about your new friend. lu.

222
00:11:19.263 --> 00:11:22.391
And if you do. there will be penalties.

223
00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:24.643
Honor among thieves.

224
00:11:25.769 --> 00:11:27.288
I'm not a thief.

225
00:11:27.312 --> 00:11:29.690
I don't know what you are yet.

226
00:11:30.357 --> 00:11:32.401
I think maybe you don't either.

227
00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:42.202
Now why don't you go get that watch?

228
00:12:09.813 --> 00:12:10.915
I can't talk to you.

229
00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:12.792
<i>Why do you keep
sending me to voicemail?</i>

230
00:12:12.816 --> 00:12:14.419
It's more polite than hanging up on you.

231
00:12:14.443 --> 00:12:16.045
<i>- Is it?</i>
- Which I'm gonna do now.

232
00:12:16.069 --> 00:12:18.339
Jack's gonna ask you to
come to his office tomorrow.

233
00:12:18.363 --> 00:12:20.175
He's gonna tell you I hired massey.

234
00:12:20.199 --> 00:12:22.051
Shit. Coop.

235
00:12:22.075 --> 00:12:24.012
Jack fucked me. Liv. You know he did.

236
00:12:24.036 --> 00:12:25.704
Massey will drag me into it.

237
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:28.433
My name will be in the papers.

238
00:12:28.457 --> 00:12:30.351
I'm not gonna let that happen.
but you will be deposed.

239
00:12:30.375 --> 00:12:32.103
I'll be the whore in the story.

240
00:12:32.127 --> 00:12:34.397
- Jack's gonna tell you to lie.
- <i>And you're telling me not to.</i>

241
00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:37.716
I'm asking you to do what's right.

242
00:12:38.550 --> 00:12:40.695
<i>He took everything from me. Liv.</i>

243
00:12:40.719 --> 00:12:42.071
And now you're gonna do that to me.

244
00:12:42.095 --> 00:12:43.239
<i>This isn't about you.</i>

245
00:12:43.263 --> 00:12:44.681
Yeah. the hell it isn't.

246
00:12:45.766 --> 00:12:46.743
I'm hanging up now.

247
00:12:46.767 --> 00:12:48.143
<i>Liv. Ple...</i>

248
00:12:49.811 --> 00:12:51.271
God. Fuck.

249
00:12:52.314 --> 00:12:54.233
- Hi. guys.
- Hey. dad.

250
00:12:54.900 --> 00:12:56.461
- Hey. dad.
- How was school?

251
00:12:56.485 --> 00:12:57.670
Same old. same old.

252
00:12:57.694 --> 00:13:00.364
- Smells good.
- Yeah. I'm making pasta.

